{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_51","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/20260312225704-impl-notes.md | sed -n '1,80p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# Implementation Notes\n     2\t\n     3\t## Decisions Made\n     4\t- Added a new `automation_runtime` context with explicit daemon task, lease, routing, journal, and loop types so daemon state is durably modeled instead of embedded in CLI code.\n     5\t- Implemented `FsDaemonStore` under `.ralph-burning/daemon/` and a `WorktreeAdapter` backed by `git worktree`/`git rebase`, with deterministic worktree paths at `.ralph-burning/worktrees/<task-id>/`.\n     6\t- Wired `daemon start/status/abort/retry/reconcile` to the existing workflow engine and stub backend stack, including single-iteration execution for deterministic CLI coverage and periodic lease heartbeats during active dispatch.\n     7\t- Added unit, conformance, and CLI coverage for routing precedence, malformed/conflicting labels, duplicate issue rejection, retry/abort behavior, reconciliation, status ordering, and single-iteration daemon execution.\n     8\t\n     9\t## Spec Deviations\n    10\t- `daemon abort` immediately cleans up claimed tasks, but active-task cleanup is deferred to the running daemon loop after cancellation so the in-use worktree is not torn down mid-dispatch.\n    11\t- Daemon dispatch switches the process working directory into the claimed worktree before invoking the workflow engine; engine-owned runtime/session persistence still uses the canonical project store paths.\n    12\t\n    13\t## Testing\n    14\t- Verified with `nix develop -c cargo test`.\n    15\t\n    16\t---\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_52","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Claimed-task cleanup on pre-dispatch failures** [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L202) [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L214)\nCurrent: After a task is claimed and its lease/worktree is created, `ensure_project(...)` and `mark_active(...)` still use `?` and can exit the daemon early without failing the task or releasing the lease. I reproduced this with an existing `standard` project plus a routed `docs_change` task on the same `project_id`: `daemon start --single-iteration` exited non-zero, left the task in `claimed`, and left both the lease JSON and writer lock on disk.\nExpected: Any failure after claim must transition the task to `failed` and release/remove the lease and worktree before returning.\nReference: Loop 11 acceptance criteria for “Task dispatch” and “Worktree lifecycle”.\n\n2. **`daemon abort` does not meet the active-task cleanup contract** [daemon.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/daemon.rs#L132) [20260312225704-impl-notes.md](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/20260312225704-impl-notes.md#L9)\nCurrent: The CLI only performs immediate lease/worktree cleanup when the original state was `claimed`. For `active` tasks it only marks the task `aborted` and returns; the implementation notes explicitly call this out as a spec deviation.\nExpected: `daemon abort <task-id>` must cancel the in-flight execution and release/remove the lease and worktree for both `claimed` and `active` tasks.\nReference: Loop 11 acceptance criterion for `daemon abort <task-id>`.\n\n3. **Polling cadence is not honored while work exists** [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L101)\nCurrent: `poll_interval` is only slept when `process_cycle()` returns `false`. If pending tasks exist, the loop immediately starts another cycle, so backlog is drained back-to-back instead of polling at the configured interval.\nExpected: `daemon start` should poll at the configured interval and process only one task per poll cycle, even when more pending tasks are queued.\nReference: Loop 11 acceptance criterion for `daemon start`.\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Add CLI/integration coverage for aborting an `active` task and for post-claim failure cleanup. `nix develop -c cargo test` is green, so these spec gaps are currently escaping through missing coverage."}}
